cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SD

The paper proposes a novel architecture and learning algorithm for unsupervised generative modeling of sequences. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and specifically involves neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions experiments on the bouncing balls generative modeling problem, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and signal processing (cs.SD).
